Highlights














How robots can work alongside - not in place of - humans
Boston, Massachusetts
 In the ongoing series, "Robotics Revolution," CBS explores how robots are transforming the way we live and work. What if machines could be a natural extension of us? Dana Jacobson reports. 









Is the American workforce ready for the Fourth Industrial Revolution?
Cary, North Carolina
 The Fourth Industrial Revolution has brought artificial intelligence, cloud computing and predictive analytics to the workplace. 









ABB to Expand Thomas & Betts and its Electrification Products Division in Memphis
Memphis, Tennessee
 Industrial and manufacturing technology leader to invest $20.7 million, create 90 new jobs. 









ABB's YuMi rings the NASDAQ opening bell
New York City, New York
 The dual arm collaborative robot was a guest of ROBO Global LLC, creator of the world’s first robotics and automaton investor index series 









The final frontier
Zurich, Switzerland
 ABB’s involvement with space technologies started in the mid-1980’s. Since then, it has been working in over 50 space programs around the world  









New Collaborative Operations Centers extend network in US and Europe
Miami, Florida
 Two new ABB Ability Collaborative Operations Centers near Miami, Florida, and Genoa, Italy are extending the company’s network. 









Faster charging key to mainstream adoption of electric vehicles
Zurich, Switzerland
 As automakers unveil more and more electric cars  that can drive four to
five times farther on a single charge than the early models five years
ago, the need to deliver a fuel station charging experience grows. 









ABB microgrid to bring clean energy and power reliability to Alaska community
Anchorage, Alaska
 ABB will provide an innovative microgrid, combining battery and flywheel
based storage technologies, designed to test scalability and improve
power stability for around 300,000 people in Anchorage, Alaska. 

















