Highlights

























ABB zenon featured in Maschinen Markt International
 The ABB zenon software has attracted interest worldwide. The German MM International –magazine
wrote about the cooperation between ABB and Copa-Data in developing this new
solution of delivering more connectivity for discrete manufacturing and machine
builders. Read more from MM International. 









Retrofit service: breathing new life into aging drives
 The best strategy is to prevent a breakdown before it happens. During the product`s life cycle, this typically means regular preventive maintenance. But for an industrial drive at the end of its life cycle, retrofit or replacement is the best solution for minimizing the risk of breakage. 









Blog post: Drive services in a digital world
 ABB remote digital service centers are set to transform industrial productivity in the era of the fourth industrial revolution 









ABB South Africa opens comprehensive regional drive service workshop
 This world-class facility aims at providing value to ABB customers all over Africa by ensuring excellent service and producing rapid turn-around time on drive units. 









 ABB at Hannover Messe 2017
 Visit us in Hannover from April 24 to 28. Hall 11, Stand A35 









Control Engineering / April 2017: Remote services can improve drive maintenance planning
 Control Engineering Europe reports on how increasing use of the Internet of Things (IoT) concept by a drives manufacturer is offering advantages for its customers. 









Ultra-low harmonic drives from ABB ensure pollution-free electricity supplies
 ABB offers a comprehensive range of ultra-low harmonic (ULH) drives to keep harmful harmonics out of all different kinds of industrial applications. 









Pipeline & Gas Journal: Driving Ahead for Secure Gas Compressor Operation
 Electrically driven gas compressors have several advantages over compressors driven by gas turbines. Read Pipeline & Gas Journal’s article to learn more. 









Why do variable speed drives fail and how do we test them?
 Kari Tikkanen, ABB Reliability Engineering Manager, describes how ABB Drives ensures that every drive lives up to high standards of reliability and add value to customers’ operations. 









ABB big data in mining and minerals
 Leonard A Eros, Global Mining Manager of ABB’s RM Division, tells World Mining Magazine’s Martin Ashcroft about the current challenges and trends in the industry. 









Blog post: Is your irrigation system equipped to realize the multiple benefits of energy efficiency?
 How to run your irrigation system smoothly and with lower electricity costs 









Business Trends: End to end industry 4.0 solutions
 Morten Wierod, Managing Director of ABB Drives  discussed the recent innovations in flexible automation, economic engineering and the food & beverage industry. 









Mining Magazine: Taking the electric avenue
 ABB looks at the potential for saving energy and emissions in mining vehicles on Mining Magazine’s latest article 









ABB PCS6000 is first medium voltage wind turbine converter to receive certification in China
 The certification confirms compliance with the Chinese full-power converter guideline for wind turbines GB/T 25387-2010 according to the CGC certification rules CGC-R46022:2011. 









Blog post: How elevators changed the world
 Elevators have had a big role in transforming the urban landscape. Learn from this blog post how ABB continuously works on improving the elevator user experience. 









Blog post: IdeaHub Innovation Challenge – the journey continues
 Thank you for the interest in ABB and the IdeaHub Innovation Challenge! 









Blog post: Engineers save the world
 Through improvements in energy efficiency, global fossil fuel consumption for power generation could be reduced by up to 30 percent. 












 
